# AI Assistant Rules for Python Virtual Environment

## Core Rules:
- ALWAYS use virtual environment for Python operations
- Check if virtual environment is activated before any Python command
- If .venv directory exists, activate it before running Python code
- Never run pip install without virtual environment activated
- Use ./.venv/Scripts/python.exe (Windows) or ./.venv/bin/python (Linux/Mac) for execution

## Before any Python execution:
1. Check if (.venv) appears in terminal prompt
2. If not activated, run: .venv\Scripts\activate.bat (Windows) or source .venv/bin/activate (Linux/Mac)
3. Verify with: which python

## Package Installation:
- Always activate virtual environment first
- Use: pip install package-name
- Never install globally

## Python Script Execution:
- Use: python script.py (after venv activation)
- Or directly: ./.venv/Scripts/python.exe script.py

## Project Structure:
- Virtual environment: .venv/
- Requirements: requirements.txt
- Keep venv isolated from system Python

